author: Justin Lahart
title: Jobs Number Leaves Fed in the Killing Yields
text:
Sure, the weak September jobs report might just be a blip. But try convincing investors of that.
The U.S. added just 142,000 nonfarm payrolls last month, the Labor Department reported Friday, with revisions to prior months taking down the nationsâ€™ job count by a further 59,000. The unemployment rate remained at 5.1%, but this came about because fewer people were looking for work rather than rising employment. Hourly wages were flat...
